    "content": "B. Use \"virtue\" in the Laozi block quote. When you are translating a quotation from a canonical text, the reader expects to recognize it against the established English renderings. Using \"character\" there would create unnecessary friction — the reader who knows the DDJ would stumble, and the reader who does not would lose the ability to cross-reference. \n\nThen when the author steps into their own analytical voice and begins working with 德 as a concept in their argument, switch to \"(constitutive) character\" with the TN explaining the departure. This respects both the canonical translation tradition and the author's distinctive philosophical usage."
